---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="DeDuper Support · Help & Troubleshooting"
  description="Get help with DeDuper. Contact support, report a bug, and find quick fixes for the most common issues on macOS."
>
  <main>

    <!-- ─── Hero ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section support-hero reveal">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="crumb mono muted">
          <a href="/deduper/">DeDuper</a> <span aria-hidden="true">/</span> Support
        </div>
        <h1>Support</h1>
        <p class="lead" style="margin-top: 16px; max-width: 520px;">
          Trouble getting DeDuper running, or found a bug? Reach out below,
          and check the quick fixes for the most common issues first.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── Get help ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section reveal" id="contact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Get in touch</h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 520px;">
          DeDuper is free and open source, maintained in my spare time. I read every
          message. Email is best for help, and GitHub is best for bugs and feature requests.
        </p>

        <div class="contact-grid">
          <div class="contact-card card">
            <div class="contact-icon">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="m3 7 9 6 9-6"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Email support</h3>
            <p>
              For setup help, questions, or anything that doesn't fit a bug report.
              I usually reply within a couple of days.
            </p>
            <a
              class="btn btn-primary contact-btn"
              href="mailto:siddharthdbobba@gmail.com?subject=DeDuper%20Support"
            >
              siddharthdbobba@gmail.com
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="contact-card card">
            <div class="contact-icon">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M21 15a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h14a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Report a bug or request a feature</h3>
            <p>
              Open an issue on GitHub. Searchable, public, and the fastest way
              to get a fix into a release.
            </p>
            <a
              class="btn btn-secondary contact-btn"
              href="https://github.com/siddharthdbobba/DeDuper/issues"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
            >
              GitHub Issues
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="report-note card">
          <strong>Filing a bug? Please include:</strong> your macOS version
          (<span class="mono"> Apple menu → About This Mac</span>), the DeDuper version
          (<span class="mono">DeDuper → About DeDuper</span>), and the steps that led to
          the problem. Screenshots help a lot. Never include the photos themselves.
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── Troubleshooting ───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section reveal" id="troubleshooting">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Common issues</h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 520px;">
          Most questions come down to one of these. If yours isn't here,
          <a class="inline-link" href="#contact">get in touch</a>.
        </p>

        <div class="help-list">
          <div class="help-item">
            <h3 class="help-q">macOS won't let me open DeDuper</h3>
            <p class="help-a">
              DeDuper is signed and notarized by Apple, so it should open normally. On the very
              first launch macOS may ask you to confirm opening an app downloaded from the internet.
              Just click <strong>Open</strong>. If it still won't open, make sure you've dragged DeDuper
              into your Applications folder first, then try again.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="help-item">
            <h3 class="help-q">DeDuper can't see my photos / no photos found</h3>
            <p class="help-a">
              macOS gates access to your library. Open
              <span class="mono">System Settings → Privacy &amp; Security → Photos</span> and turn on
              DeDuper, then relaunch the app. For scanning a local folder, grant access when prompted,
              or add DeDuper under <span class="mono">Privacy &amp; Security → Files and Folders</span> /
              <span class="mono">Full Disk Access</span>.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="help-item">
            <h3 class="help-q">Scanning is slow or looks stuck</h3>
            <p class="help-a">
              The first scan of a large library takes the longest, since DeDuper builds a perceptual hash for
              every photo. Progress can pause on big videos or RAW files. Leave it running; subsequent
              scans are much faster. If it never finishes, email me with your library size and macOS version.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="help-item">
            <h3 class="help-q">It flagged too many (or too few) duplicates</h3>
            <p class="help-a">
              Tune the sensitivity (conservative, balanced, or aggressive) and the time window
              (default 30 seconds) in settings. Conservative flags only near-identical shots taken
              moments apart; aggressive casts a wider net. Favorites and any albums you mark as
              protected are never touched.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="help-item">
            <h3 class="help-q">I deleted photos I wanted to keep</h3>
            <p class="help-a">
              Nothing is permanently erased. Photos removed from your Apple Photos library go to the
              <strong>Recently Deleted</strong> album, recoverable for 30 days; files removed from a local
              folder go to the <strong>Trash</strong>. To decide before anything is removed at all, turn on
              <strong>Hold for review</strong>, and DeDuper will move flagged photos to a review album instead
              of deleting them.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="help-item">
            <h3 class="help-q">How do I update DeDuper?</h3>
            <p class="help-a">
              Download the latest <span class="mono">.dmg</span> from the
              <a class="inline-link" href="/deduper/#download">download page</a>
              and drag it over the old copy in Applications. Your settings and protected albums normally carry over.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="help-item">
            <h3 class="help-q">Is my data private?</h3>
            <p class="help-a">
              Yes. DeDuper has no network access, so your photos and their metadata never leave your device.
              Grouping, scoring, and close-call resolution all run on-device. There are no accounts, no
              uploads, and no tracking. You can verify this yourself in the
              <a class="inline-link" href="https://github.com/siddharthdbobba/DeDuper" target="_blank" rel="noopener">open source</a>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── Quick links ───────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section reveal" id="links">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Quick links</h2>
        <div class="links-row">
          <a class="link-chip card" href="/downloads/DeDuper.dmg" download>
            <span class="link-chip-title">Download the latest version</span>
            <span class="mono muted">DeDuper.dmg · 1.6 MB ↓</span>
          </a>
          <a class="link-chip card" href="https://github.com/siddharthdbobba/DeDuper" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            <span class="link-chip-title">View the source</span>
            <span class="mono muted">github.com/siddharthdbobba/DeDuper ↗</span>
          </a>
          <a class="link-chip card" href="/deduper/#features">
            <span class="link-chip-title">How DeDuper works</span>
            <span class="mono muted">features &amp; FAQ →</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── Back ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section back-section">
      <div class="container" style="text-align: center;">
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/deduper/">← Back to DeDuper</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  /* Hero */
  .support-hero { padding-top: 72px; padding-bottom: 48px; }
  .crumb        { margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 0.85rem; }
  .crumb a      { color: var(--muted); transition: color 0.15s; }
  .crumb a:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  .inline-link  { color: var(--accent); }
  .inline-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  /* Contact */
  .contact-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
    max-width: 620px;
  }
  .contact-card { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }
  .contact-icon {
    width: 44px; height: 44px;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1; color: #fff;
    background: var(--grad);
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 20px -8px rgba(59,130,246,0.55);
  }
  .contact-card p { font-size: 0.9rem; flex: 1; }
  .contact-btn  { margin-top: 4px; align-self: flex-start; }

  .report-note {
    max-width: 620px;
    margin-top: 16px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius) var(--radius) 0;
  }

  /* Troubleshooting */
  .help-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0; }
  .help-item { padding: 20px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .help-item:first-child { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .help-q { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text); }
  .help-a { font-size: 0.9rem; max-width: 620px; }

  /* Quick links */
  .links-row { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; max-width: 560px; }
  .link-chip {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 16px;
    padding: 18px 22px;
  }
  .link-chip-title { font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .link-chip .mono { font-size: 0.78rem; }

  /* Back */
  .back-section { padding-top: 32px; padding-bottom: 48px; }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .contact-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .support-hero { padding-top: 48px; }
    .link-chip { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 6px; }
  }
</style>
